(xii)  take  the  lead  in  preparing  the  road  map  for  institutional  reform  and  human 
resources development; and 
(xiii)  assist the executing agency in coordinating potential public relations issues. 

C.  Deputy Team Leader and Environmental Human Resources Specialist (national, 7 
person-months) 

4.  The deputy team leader and/or environmental human resources specialist should have (i) 
at least 8 years of experience in human resources related to environmental administration in the 
PRC, (ii) demonstrated experience in policy analysis development of indicator systems, and (iii) 
English language proficiency and demonstrated experience in compiling technical reports and 
other  outputs  similar  to  what  is  expected  in  this  TA.  The  deputy  team  leader  and/or 
environmental human resources specialist will 
(i)  prepare  a  situational  analysis  on  the  current  human  resources  capacity  in 
environmental protection in the PRC; 
(ii)  establish  an  indicator  system  for  capacity  assessment,  current  capacity 
assessment,  analysis  of  training  requirements,  and  analysis  of  policies  and 
mechanisms relating to the cultivation of environmental protection skills;  
(iii)  review existing policies on training for environmental protection personnel and 
the effectiveness of current trainings conducted;  
(iv)  provide specific recommendations on establishing a system for human resources 
development and management;
